 Five people died, including two Pakistani nationals, horror crash on the N4 in Rustenburg. The incident occurred 19km towards Rustenburg along the N4 road from Swartruggens. Two cars collided and five occupants were declared dead at the scene and others were rushed to a nearby hospital by emergency ambulances. Community Safety and Transport Management MEC Sello Lehari sent condolences to the deceased families and wishes speedy recovery to the injured. The MEC is in Rustenburg accompanying Police Minister Bheki Cele who is conducting Safer Festive Season Operations in the Province. Lehari appealled to motorists to be patient and obey all road rules. "Avoid unnecessary overtaking and speeding. â€œThe MEC implores all driving in and through the Province to be responsible drivers and help to reduce the fatalities." 